      "Landscaping insurance in Arizona typically costs $800-$3,000 annually for general liability, depending on your services, revenue, equipment value, and number of employees. Pesticide application may require additional coverage.",
  },
  {
    question: "Does my insurance cover damage from irrigation work?",
    answer:
      "Yes, general liability insurance covers property damage from irrigation installation or repair work. This includes flooding, pipe damage, and landscape damage from faulty irrigation systems.",
